from their scheduled--

A:  Yeah, I got a little concerned that I may  have to drive myself to the
airport or I may have--I   may have checked to see if Kato was home and told
him  to do it.

Q:   Well, do you have a recollection now of  checking with Kato to see if he
was home--

A:  No. I said the limo hadn't come.

Q:   Excuse me, Mr. Simpson. Do you have--

A:  I can't have a recollection of something  just told you. If he hadn't  of
come, I would   have -- I was thinking at the time I would have driven  myself
or I would have asked Kato to take me to the   airport, and since he had come
before I was ready to  go, I didn't have to do those things.

Q:  Okay. So that we're clear, at some point, 10:35, 10:40, you began to be
