a double murder investigation. Is that true?

A: Not necessarily, no.

Q: All right. Well, where am I wrong?

MR. BAKER: The question is vague. Could call for a narrative.

THE WITNESS: The sequence of events was such that I didn't put
everything together at the time I saw these events transpiring, but I
didn't make hard-and-fast conclusions at this time. Everything was
just a whirlwind, and so I really didn't leave and say, "Aha, he's a
suspect." I didn't have that thought.

BY MR. BREWER:

