MS. LEVINE: The thought process that we went through on this, if that
helps you any, is that there are certain calls on here that you might
see that are like obviously personal calls, like a family member,
which might be denoted by a family member, but there may have been-it
was our belief that there may have been some conversation in that call
regarding what  occurred and so we left it in, as opposed to things
that were purely business that wouldn't have had anything whatsoever
to do with that.

And so when there is a call, for example, from a family member but it
was our belief that it may have had some conversational content
related to the issues involved here, they were left in.

MR. PETROCELLI: So every single entry in this Exhibit 203 in some way
relates to the murder of Nicole and/or O.J. Simpson. True?

MS. LEVINE: May -- what I was saying, it may have. We couldn't recall
exactly what they were, so some of them that may have. For example,
there is one that says a "Uncle Bob." There is a belief that it could
have, although we couldn't recall.

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Do you adopt your lawyer's statements about the description of this
document?

A: Yes.

Q: Okay. On the first page, the calendar, on June 13, there is an
entry at 1:00 o'clock that's crossed out. Does that have anything to
do with this  matter?

A: No. That was a lunch meeting I had --

Q: That you canceled?

A: -- that didn't transpire.

Q: And "Mark Boone," he is a business acquaintance?

A: Yes.

Q: Does he know O.J. Simpson?

A: No.

Q: Okay. And the next day, on the 14th, you have another entry crossed
out, "Frank Baker?

A: Yes.

Q: Now, why were those entries left on here?

MS. LEVINE: Because they were canceled because of him doing things
related to this --

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Okay. Is that true?

A: That's correct.

Q: And is the same true of the 12:00 o'clock Ben Littlefield lunch on
the 16th?

A: That was business, correct.

Q: Okay. Does he have anything to do with Mr. Simpson?

A: No.

Q: Okay. Underneath that there is a redaction, and underneath the
redaction there is something I can't read. What does that say?

A: It looks like "viewing."

MS. LEVINE: "Nicole's body," is what I read it as, "View Nicole's
body."

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Okay. Turn the page. On the 16th it says "Studio." What does that
relate to?

A: That relates to Movie Tunes.

Q: Nothing to do with this. Right?

A: No.

Q: Then underneath that it says, "Nicole's funeral." Right?

A: Correct

Q: Okay. And on the first page of this calendar there is an entry on
June 9 Thursday. It says "9:00," and I can't read what it says.

A: I have no idea.

Q: Something "McCoy."

A: Looks like "Granger."

Q: Yeah.

A: But I don't know who that is.

Q: And what does that have to do with this matter?

A: Nothing as far as I know. I don't know who it is.

Q: Okay. You don't know why that was left on here then?

A: No.

Q: And under June 11, Saturday, there is something to the right of
Saturday that I can't read.

A: That's my niece's birthday, and then I went to Fresno on the 11th
and 12th.

Q: "AII 4 kids with me"?

A: "A114 kids with me." We went to Fresno.

Q: Okay. On the incoming calls for June 13, are these people who
called you relating to the murder of Nicole called you to talk about
or inquire --

A: Or inquire, yes.

Q: Is that accurate?

A: Yes.

Q: Kimberly is whom?

A: My daughter.

Q: Bob is your uncle?

A: Correct.

Q: Mark Boone?

A: Is-he's really a business associate.

Q: Helen?

A: My mother.

Q: Bruce Brandon?

A: He's a friend in Orange County.

Q: Tommy is your brother?

A: Correct.

Q: And in all these conversations people were inquiring about what was
going on. Right?

A: Correct.

Q: And on the next page, the outgoing calls, "Frank Babern?

A: That's correct.

Q: And you included these because you spoke to him about the
situation?

A: No. I don't know why those are there. Those were -- he was from my 
law school. They wanted me to speak at the law school, and that's why
he was calling, and we were trying to reach him to cancel my speech.

Q: On the 14th of June who is Sheila?

A: Sheila [Name Deleted].

Q: Randy's wife?

A: Randy [Name Deleted]'s wife.

Q: Neil Hersh is whom.'

A: He's my divorce attorney.

Q: Michael is whom?

A: My associate that worked with  me -- works with me. Michael Ameen.

A Joni?

A: She's a personal friend on mine.

Q: What's her last name?

A: Pulvers.

Q: "That's the name under "Joni"?

A: That looks like my aunt.

Q: Okay. Down at the end, Barbara is your sister?

A: My sister, yes.

Q: And who is Rod Sherman?

A: He's an acquaintance.

Q: A friend?

A: Football player from SC, uh-huh.

Q: Al Rodriguez?

A: Same thing. He's an acquaintance.

Q: Allen Ostroff?

A: That's business. That shouldn't be there. That's business. I did
not speak to any of these people.

Q: On the 15th, Alan Austin?

A: Right.

Q: He's a friend of yours?

A: He's a friend of O.J.'s.

Q: Okay. And what did he call -- what did you and he talk about on the
15th of June?

A: He would just be calling to inquire --

MS. LEVINE: Don't speculate if you can't recall what he called about.

THE WITNESS: I don't know. He called constantly just to inquire as to
what was going on.

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Okay. Carolyn Cadish?

A: She's a friend from Chicago or somewhere back there.

Q: Uncle Bobby is an uncle of yours?

A: Correct.

Q: Bob Chandler is a friend of yours?

A: Yes.

Q: Denise Brown, you spoke to her, on the 15th?

A: No, I did not speak to her. This -- she could have been calling for
O.J., not for me. I don't speak to Denise Brown that often.

Q: Did you speak to the Browns on the telephone at all that week?

A: I did not, no.

Q: Okay. Do you know whether Mr. Simpson did?

A: Yes, I know he did.

Q: Okay. Jerry Tolman?

A: That's business.

Q: Okay. And Bill Clark?

A: Business also.

Q: Arthur Kardashian?

A: That's my father.

Q: Brian Avnet?

A: That's business.

Q: Why did you include the American Airlines item?

A: I don't know where I was going. "Ticket is refundable." I don't
know.

Q: On June 16, who is David McKenna?

A: He's a friend of mine from law school.

Q: Who are Bridgette and Tanacio Felix?

A: Those are friends of O.J.'s.

Q: On the 17th you spoke to Marcus Allen?

A: No, I did not. It could have been - O.J. could have, but I did not.

Q: Do you remember Mr. Simpson speaking to Marcus Allen? ;

A: No, I don't.

Q: Now, if the call came in for Mr. Simpson, was it recorded on these
incoming call sheets?

A: Sometimes - yes, sometimes they would be.

Q: And how would the person --

A: It was sporadic.

Q: And how would the person get Mr. Simpson on the phone? Just call
upstairs?

A: It was intercommed to either his room or wherever he was located.

Q: Okay. And this is Barbara and Nicole Pulvers who were faking these
calls?

A: Yes, sir.

Q: Okay. Who is third-fourth name down, somebody "Brown"?

A: Looks like "Judy Brown".

Q: Okay. Helene, is that your mother?

A: That's my mother.

Q: Okay. "Joan" on the next page?

A: Joan is my sister-in-law.

Q: Okay. Paula. You spoke to Paul?

A: No, I did not.

Q: But she called?

A: Evidently.

Q: Looks like she called several times.

A: Evidently, yes.

Q: Barbara Walters called you that day?

A: Yes. I was amazed she got my number.

Q: Who is Mark Kurian?

A: Oh, he's just a kid, a friend of my children.

Q: Who is Celeste? Someone who works for Wayne Hughes?

A: No. That's a cousin of mine.

Q: Now go to the next page. It indicates that somebody placed a call
to Marcus Allen at  9: 10, an outgoing call.

A: That was not me. That would have been Mr. Simpson.

Q: And do you know what he and Mr. Allen discussed at 9:10 on the
morning of the 17th of June?

A: I do not.

Q: You attended a meeting at Mr. Shapiro's office, I believe you
previously testified, with a lot of Mr. Simpson's friends in
attendance?

A: Yes.

Q: And that's a meeting that Cathy Randa called people to attend?

A: Yes.

MS. LEVINE: Can I have a date on this?

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: This is a meeting that occurred when?

A: I don't know. I think shortly after

Q: Shortly after --

A: June or July, right -- beginning of July.

Q: Mr. Simpson's arrest?

A: Correct.

Q: And this was in Mr. Shapiro's office?

A: Yes, in his conference room.

Q: And there were a number of people there. Right?

A: Yes.

Q: And people were phoned in as well, correct, conference-called in?

A: Correct.

Q: And Simpson was on the line from the jail cell?

A: Correct.

Q: And he was on the speakerphone?

A: Yes.

Q: And he spoke to everybody in that room. Right?

A: That's correct.

Q: And Mr. Shapiro spoke as well. Right?

A: Yes.

Q: And did you speak?

A: Other than to say hello, I don't think I did.

Q: Okay. And tell us what was discussed at that meeting.

A: It was to get support, funds to pay attorneys, to have basic
support if anybody knew anything. Just really aid and assistance in
his case.

Q: And Mr. Simpson talked to most of the people individually in that
room. Right?

A: I think they passed-yeah, he did. I think they went around the
table and everybody said who they were, and he said, "Thanks for
coming," or...

Q: And one of the messages given was to try to support Mr. Simpson
through this ordeal. Right?

A: Yes.

Q: And also not to talk to anyone. Right?

A: It could have -- I don't recall. It could have been, "Don't talk "
-

MS. LEVINE: Don't speculate . BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Don't talk. Right?

MS. LEVINE: Do your recall or do you not recall?

THE WITNESS: No, I think so. Not to talk to the press.

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: And anyone else. Right?

A: I think it was press.

Q: Including the police. Right?

A: That I don't recall, no.

Q: In other words, Mr. Shapiro told everyone at this meeting that they
should not talk to investigators, press, police, anyone, unless --

MS. LEVINE: That misstates the testimony. He just said not -- he
doesn't recall him saying not to talk to the police.

MR. PETROCELLI: I don't have to accept that answer. I can press on. I
don't believe that answer, and I'm probing to see if I can demonstrate
that it's not true.

MR. BAKER: Judge, juror and advocate.

MR. PETROCELLI: No. It's my job.

MS. LEVINE: Well, it's argumentative then, and it's compound.

MR. PETROCELLI: Maybe it is. Maybe it's not. That's an objection the
judge will rule on.

MS. LEVINE: Well, a compound question, he can't answer. That's a
question that needs to be dealt -- objection that needs to be dealt
with here. He testified-

MR. PETROCELLI: Are you going to instruct him not to answer that
question?

MS. LEVINE: Yeah, I am going to instruct him not to answer that
question.

BY MR. PETROCELLI:

Q: Okay. At this meeting Mr. Shapiro told the assembled mass not to
talk to anyone. True?

A: True.

Q: Thank you. Okay. That's all we have for now. We will have a
stipulation that --

MR. BAKER: That the original is sent to Miss Levine -- well, the
original will be sent to Miss-

MR. PETROCELLI: Anyway, we have the normal stipulation: The original
to Miss Levine. 30 days upon your receipt to advise us if there are
any  changes and if the witness has signed the transcript. If it's not
signed and we are not so informed within 30 days of your receipt, then
a copy can be used for all purposes in lieu of an original, and the
court reporter otherwise is relieved of the statutory duties.

So stipulated?

MS. LEVINE: Return to you?

MR. PETROCELLI: Yeah.

MS. LEVINE: So stipulated.

MR. PETROCELLI: I will say this on the record, though: I am probably
going to set a motion to be heard on January- excuse me-on June 5,
which is a date that we are setting a number of motions in this case
to compel further answers, and I just want to give everyone ample
notice of that.

MS. LEVINE: I have to check my calendar because this isn't the only
case -the case that I have number one on my list.

MR. PETROCELLI: Believe it or not, it's not my only case either.

MS. LEVINE: No, but it's probably higher in your priority list.

MR. PETROCELLI: Well, in the presence of my client, I would have to
safe you are absolutely correct.

MR. LEONARD: Dan, we're still on the record.

MR. PETROCELLI: Oh, we are? Okay. We are off the record now.

THE VIDEOGRAPHER: This concludes the deposition of Robert Kardashian,
Volume II. The number of videotapes used was three. We are going off
the record, and the time is approximately 5:10.

(ENDING TIME: 5:10 P.M.)

I DECLARE UNDER PENALTY OF PERJURY THAT THE FOREGOING IS TRUE AND
CORRECT. SUBSCRIBED AT CALIFORNIA, THIS DAY OF ,19_. ROBERT G.
KARDASHIAN
