<HTML><HEAD> <TITLE>Court TV Casefiles</TITLE> </HEAD> <BODY

TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> <A

HREF="/map/casefiles.map"><IMG

SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/casefiles.gif" ISMAP ALT="Court TV

Casefiles" BORDER="0"></A> <BR CLEAR=ALL> <P>Writer, director and

producer Lawrence Schiller visited O.J. Simpson 16 times at the Los

Angeles County Jail in November and December of 1994. Schiller, a

former neighbor who once directed Simpson in a music video, gained

access to Simpson as a possible material witness in the criminal

trial. But those visits were primarily used to produce, "I Want to

Tell You," a book in which Simpson answers letters from the public and

proclaims his innocence. Royalties from the book, which received a $1

million advance, were paid to Simpson's legal defense fund. In this

June 7, 1996 deposition, lawyers for the family of Ronald Goldman

asked about the 30 hours of interviews recorded in producing

the book.</P><HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT> <PRE>



COURT OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA FOR THE COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES 



SHARON RUFO, Plaintiff



vs.



ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, et al., Defendants



DEPOSITION OF LAWRENCE J. SCHILLER Los Angeles, California June 7,

1996



DAVID S. COLEMAN CSR #4613 JOB NO. 96-1653



SUPERIOR COURT OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA FOR THE COUNTY OF LOS

ANGELES



SHARON RUFO, Plaintiff



vs.



ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, et al., Defendants



FREDRIC GOLDMAN, etc., et al., Plaintiff



vs.



ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, et al., Defendants.



LOUIS H. BROWN, etc., Plaintiffs,



vs.



ORENTHAL JAMES SIMPSON, Defendant.



Deposition of LAWRENCE J. SCHILLER, taken on behalf of the Plaintiffs,

At 11377 West Olympic Boulevard, 10th Floor, Los Angeles, California,

commencing at 9:27 a m., on Friday, June 7, 1996 before David S.

Coleman, CSR #4613, pursuant to Notice and Subpoena



APPEARANCES:



FOR THE PLAINTIFFS FREDRIC GOLDMAN, ET AL.: 

MITCHELL, SILBERBERG & KNUPP BY: 

PETER B. GELBLUM, ESQ. ARTHUR GROMAN, ESQ. 11377 West

Olympic Boulevard Sixth Floor Los Angeles, California 90064-1883



FOR THE PLAINTIFF ESTATE OF BROWN: 

