curious.



Q: What was who like?



A: What was Nicole like, what were they like  together. She was

curious. She wanted to know. That was it. She never really asked about

the actual killing.



Q: You are talking about questions that she  asked you, what were

Nicole and O.J. like?



A: Yeah. Were they happy, what was going on  with them at the time.



Q: She asked you these questions after Nicole's murder. Right?



A: Yes.



Q: And what was going on at the time between  them and so forth.

Right?



A: What was their -- what was the state of  their affairs, you know,

the kids, what was it like,  you know, with the divorce and

everything, were they  together, were they apart.



Q: What did you say to her?



A: On what questions?



Q: In answers to all those questions.



MR. LEONARD: Objection. It's overbroad --



THE WITNESS: Say yes, no, maybe. Which questions?



MR.LEONARD: It's -- objection --



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Tell me --



MR.LEONARD: Objection. It's overbroad. It's vague. You know, if you

