about her father?



A: Yeah.



Q: And did she ever complain about him?



A: Sometimes.



Q: What would she say?



A: "Dad is being dorky," or "goofy" or  whatever. But not -- I mean,

not like "I hate him" or  anything like that.



Q: So from your observations, there was a  normal relationship there?



A: Yes.



Q: And with Justin also?



A: Justin, yeah.



Q: Okay. Did you ever see your father spank either Sydney or Justin?



A: I've never seen it, no.



Q: Last time you were hit by your father was when you were how old?



A: I don't remember. I mean, I gotta guess.



Q: 14, you said?



A: I'd have to guess. I'd say 14.



Q: Did he ever hit you with anything other than a belt?



A: Never.



Q: Okay. Let's go back to the telephone call that you had with Nicole

on June 12. Who called  whom?



A: I don't remember. I probably called her, though, I would think,

just to find out exactly how  many people were coming, you know, that

whole thing.  I think I did call her, actually, to find out exactly 

how many people, if they wanted like, you know, a  fixed menu. "What

time do you think you guys are going to be there?"



Q: What did she say to you?



A: What?



Q: Tell me what she said after you called  her.



A: She said she didn't think that they were  gonna be swinging by

Jackson's because it was just too expensive, and the kids, by the time

they got way out there, they're gonna be all restless, and by the --

you know, "We're just gonna have dinner up the street."



I mean, she went to Mezzaluna all the time so it was just easier for

her. I figured okay, fine go. I was kinda hurt; I wish they would have

come to the restaurant, but now I really wish they would have come to

the restaurant, but she wanted to go to Mezzaluna.



Q: Did she tell you that O.J. Simpson would be going to the dinner?



A: She -- no, it never came up.



Q: That didn't come up?



A: It didn't. Because actually I was calling to find out how many

people and who was coming, so once I found out they weren't gonna be

coming at all, it was moot.



Q: When you first spoke to her about coming to Jackson's either Friday

or Saturday before the 12th, did she tell you that Mr. Simpson would

be attending this dinner?



A: She never -- that was never brought up.



Q: Your understanding was that the whole  family would be coming, and

if he was at the recital, he would come also. Right?



MR. LEONARD: Objection --



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Excuse me?



MR. LEONARD:-- lack of foundation.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



You may answer.



A: Yeah, I would assume he would be there if he was in town.



