Q: It wasn't 17 years, in other words --



A: Oh, okay.



Q: -- that you lived with them.



THE VIDEOGRAPHER: We are going off the record now, and the time is

approximately 4:42.



(Pause in the proceedings.)



THE VIDEOGRAPHER: We are back on the record and the time is

approximately 4:43.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Your father was -- is a jealous man, is  he not?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Lack of foundation,  calls for speculation.

It's vague.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: You can answer.



A: I don't think he's any more jealous than the next guy.



Q: He is a jealous guy -- he was a jealous guy when it came to Nicole.

Is that a fair statement?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Lack of foundation, calls for speculation,

argumentative.



THE WITNESS: Like I said, I don't think he' more jealous than the next

guy.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Yeah, but I'm not asking you that.



A: Well, I've never seen him do anything that --



Q: Did you regard him as a jealous man when  it came towards Nicole?



MR. LEONARD: Objection --



THE WITNESS: No, I wouldn't regard him as a  jealous man.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: A controlling guy --



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Vague.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: -- when it came to Nicole?



A: Maybe a little controlling.



Q: He's a controlling person in general. Is that a fair statement.'



A: Not in general.



Q: Towards Nicole he was. Right?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Vague as to "controlling."



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: You can answer.



A: Toward Nicole, no, I wouldn't -- toward a couple things. I mean...



Q: Like what?



A: Conversations. Talk to him, he likes to -- you know, he likes to

head the conversation usually.



Q: What else?



A: What else. Let's see. He's an opinionated guy. And that's all I

could think about right now. And, yeah, with Nicole sometimes.



Q: How did Nicole treat your father when she  was alive?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Vague.



THE WITNESS: She treated him well.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Your father wrote in his so-called suicide note that he was a

battered spouse or he was  the battered one in the relationship, words

to that effect. Do you recall that?



A: I recall it, yes.



Q: Did you see any evidence of that?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Lack of foundation, calls for speculation.



THE WITNESS: Battered, no. I wouldn't call it battered.



BY MR. PETROCELLI:



Q: Do you know what he meant by that?



A: Yeah, I do.



Q: What did he mean?



A: I think he felt that -- in my opinion, I  think he felt that he

also sustained some abuse, but whether it be mental or even physical,

but it doesn't matter. I mean, he's bigger than her, so it -- like I

-- it doesn't matter.



You know, I mean, Nicole is a smaller white woman. He is a bigger

black man. You will  never, ever, no matter what, no matter in what

court,  in what country, in what land, if these two people  fight,

there's no way that he will ever, you know, be  looked at with any

kind of sympathy. I think that's  what he might have thought when he

wrote that.



Q: How was he abused by Nicole?



A: Abused? I don't know. You'd have to ask him that.



Q: You said you think that what he was referring to is that he had

sustained some abuse.



A: Nicole, I mean -- Nicole -- Nicole, I mean, she was a great person

and everything like that, she wasn't just a flower. I mean, you can

get into arguments with Nicole. I mean, Nicole was a pretty

hard-headed person herself.



Q: Did you see her abuse your father?



MR. LEONARD: Objection. Vague.



THE WITNESS: No, I never saw her abuse my dad.



MR. PETROCELLI: No further questions.



We will have a stipulation that the original of the transcript will be

sent to Mr. Baker's  firm?



MR. LEONARD: (Nods head.)



MR. PETROCELLI: And that you will have 30 days  thereafter within

which to inform us of any changes or  corrections and whether the

witness has signed it, and  if it's not signed within 30 days after

receipt by  Baker's firm, then the transcript can be used for all 

purposes -- a copy of the transcript can be used for  all purposes as

though signed.



MR. LEONARD: Agreed.



MR. PETROCELLI: Thank you.



THE WITNESS: Thanks.



THE VIDEOGRAPHER: This concludes the deposition of Jason Simpson. The

number of videotapes used was three. We are going off the record, and

the  time is approximately 4:48.



(ENDING TIME: 4:48 P.M.) I DECLARE UNDER PENALTY OF PERJURY THAT THE

FOREGOING IS TRUE AND CORRECT.



SUBSCRIBED AT



CALIFORNIA, THIS _ DAY OF 19 ___.



JASON LAMAR SIMPSON



</PRE>

